    {
      "game": "celeste",
      "name": "Spumperest Peak",
      "difficulty": "Advanced",
      "description": "our first map!! this was made as an unofficial sequel to Spumperer Peak by Jitio, which was an unofficial sequel to Spumper Peak by sunsetquasar, which was an unoffical sequel to The Summit by Maddy Thorson, which was an official sequel to chapters 1-6 of hit video game Celeste by EXOK Games. This map has THREE different endings for you to get, ranging from Advanced to something higher than that, so good luck and have fun in this atrocity!",
      "video": "https://youtu.be/iyEf0y_96eE",
      "date": "2026-04-18T20:13:45.893Z",
      "link": "https://gamebanana.com/mods/604316",
      "diff_order": 5
    },
    {
      "game": "celeste",
      "name": "Dreams Of A Night Sky",
      "difficulty": "Yellow Beginner",
      "description": "this map was dubbed as \"the first ever illegal golden.\" i will not go in depth as to why this is, but it is a tier 1 and i would highly recommend it! i am quite proud of the decoration in this one, however the gameplay cut off quickly due to a lack of ideas.",
      "video": "https://youtu.be/nM1hM614CM4",
      "date": "2026-04-18T20:29:50.715Z",
      "link": "https://gamebanana.com/mods/647148",
      "diff_order": 6
    },
    {
      "game": "celeste",
      "name": "The Hanging Garden",
      "difficulty": "Yellow Expert",
      "description": "from gamebanana: \"this map is a forgotten, unfinished project of mine from a couple months ago. rather than letting it sit, i decided to make a stupid final room and release it as is. enjoy!\" basically this is saying that this map is unpolished and not the best! after learning that the petals found in Garden of Khu'tara were just extended variant triggers, we decided we wanted to put our own spin on it! we had a couple ideas for it but sadly it fell a bit short. ignore the last two rooms please they are fake.",
      "video": "https://youtu.be/BNZvdSTjXOw",
      "date": "2026-04-18T20:31:07.081Z",
      "link": "https://gamebanana.com/mods/647538",
      "diff_order": 4
    },
    {
      "game": "celeste",
      "name": "commatose",
      "difficulty": "Red Grandmaster",
      "description": "commatose is a failed GM+1 map based around crouch climbs. it contains three main screens and a tutorial + heart room, and it has recieved very mixed opinions enjoyment wise. upon release, Jade downloaded the map and completely obliterated my sense of difficulty by clearing it in seven minutes. issy also ended up doing the same but by getting the golden! overall, i like how this turned out, and i will never map crouch climbs again!",
      "video": "https://youtu.be/THrQ7UJsdps",
      "date": "2026-04-18T20:32:44.196Z",
      "link": "https://gamebanana.com/mods/654048",
      "diff_order": 3
    },
    {
      "game": "celeste",
      "name": "ANGELICIDE",
      "difficulty": "Red Grandmaster+2",
      "description": "ANGELICIDE is by far the hardest map we have ever made, and it was by complete accident. it consists of a single high GM moce-like screen that we made freezeframeless, meaning that nearly every setup in the map was removed, and the player would have to hit several pixel-perfect gaps. as stated in the map description, \"This maps sole intention is to make fun of times where people will artificially buff a level (mostly in GD) by adding fixed hitboxes, buffing to match a click pattern, etc.\" good luck if you try to clear this.",
      "video": "https://youtu.be/OKJ-euuBufk",
      "date": "2026-04-18T21:00:00.551Z",
      "link": "https://gamebanana.com/mods/656794",
